# Accepted Trivy IaC findings. Add one rule ID per line with a justification.
# Example:
# AVD-AWS-0057  # CloudWatch log retention left to default for dev cost reasons

# EKS API endpoint is publicly reachable. Required: the GitHub Actions CI role
# (terraform + kubectl via the addons/helm providers) reaches the cluster API
# over the public internet — there is no self-hosted runner in the VPC. Private
# endpoint would break the pipeline. Revisit if/when runners move into the VPC.
AVD-AWS-0040  # EKS public cluster access enabled — needed for GitHub-hosted CI
AVD-AWS-0041  # EKS public access CIDR 0.0.0.0/0 — GitHub runner IPs are dynamic

# Unrestricted egress (0.0.0.0/0) on security groups. Standard for nodes/NLB that
# must reach AWS APIs, ECR, and the internet; egress filtering is not part of this
# project's threat model.
AVD-AWS-0104  # Unrestricted egress — accepted default for cluster/NLB SGs
